Database Schema

Here's a suggested database schema with the main tables and their relationships:

    blocks - Stores information about each block.

    id (Primary Key)
    block_height (Unique)
    block_hash (Unique)
    parent_block_hash
    timestamp
    miner_address
    block_reward
    difficulty
    num_transactions
    total_transaction_volume

    transactions - Stores information about each transaction.

    id (Primary Key)
    tx_hash (Unique)
    block_id (Foreign Key to blocks)
    from_address
    to_address
    amount
    fee
    nonce
    timestamp

    addresses - Stores information about each address.

    id (Primary Key)
    address (Unique)
    balance

    address_transactions - Stores the relationship between addresses and transactions.

    id (Primary Key)
    address_id (Foreign Key to addresses)
    transaction_id (Foreign Key to transactions)

    tokens - Stores information about each token/asset (if applicable).

    id (Primary Key)
    contract_address (Unique)
    name
    symbol
    decimals
    total_supply

    token_holders - Stores the relationship between tokens and their holders.

    id (Primary Key)
    token_id (Foreign Key to tokens)
    address_id (Foreign Key to addresses)
    balance

You can customize this schema based on the specific requirements of your blockchain explorer and the blockchain network you're targeting.